<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="510" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,865,1033]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,901,925]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Remarks.</emphasis>
Specimens of this species were not available for study. It was recorded, without figures, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,901,925]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[158,244,937,961]" name="Taiwan" pageId="9" pageNumber="510">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
) by Dai, Li &amp; Chen (
<number box="[514,576,937,961]" pageId="9" pageNumber="510" value="2004.0">2004</number>
). The species can be distinguished by the following features: pygophore extended and tapered posteriorly with pair of small dorsoposterior processes; stem of connective equal to arms in length; aedeagus with basal apodeme expanded, shaft slightly sinuate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
